      "title": "The Importance of Daily Exercise for Dogs",
      "type": "Lifestyle",
      "content": "Physical activity is crucial for a dog’s overall well-being, as it helps maintain a healthy weight, builds strong muscles, and supports cardiovascular health. Lack of exercise can lead to behavioral problems such as excessive barking, chewing, or anxiety. Different breeds have varying exercise needs: high-energy breeds like Border Collies or Labradors may require 1-2 hours of vigorous activity per day, including running, playing fetch, or agility training. On the other hand, smaller or less active breeds might need only moderate daily walks. Incorporating mental stimulation through puzzle toys and training sessions is also vital, as it prevents boredom and promotes obedience."
