      "title": "How to Properly Clean Your Bird’s Cage",
      "type": "Care",
      "content": "Maintaining a clean environment is essential for the health of pet birds, as dirty cages can harbor bacteria, mold, and parasites that cause respiratory issues and infections. Cage cleaning should involve daily removal of uneaten food, droppings, and soiled bedding. Once a week, perform a deep clean by disassembling removable parts and washing them with warm water and a mild, non-toxic cleaner or a vinegar-water solution. Avoid harsh chemicals like bleach. Clean toys, perches, and feeding dishes thoroughly to prevent disease transmission. Providing fresh cage liners and ensuring proper ventilation will help keep your bird happy and healthy."
