      "id": 4,
      "title": "Grooming Tips for Long-Haired Cats",
      "type": "Care",
      "content": "Long-haired cats require consistent grooming to prevent mats and tangles that can cause discomfort and skin infections. Use a wide-toothed comb or slicker brush to gently detangle fur, focusing on problem areas such as the belly, behind the ears, and under the legs. Grooming sessions should ideally occur every other day to reduce shedding and hairball formation. Regular grooming also helps distribute natural oils along the coat, enhancing shine and skin health. If mats form, carefully cut them out or seek professional grooming to avoid hurting your cat."
