      "title": "The Benefits of Interactive Toys for Pets",
      "type": "Entertainment",
      "content": "Interactive toys are designed to engage pets mentally and physically, which is essential for preventing boredom-related behaviors like destructive chewing or excessive vocalization. Puzzle feeders encourage pets to work for their food, stimulating problem-solving skills and slowing down rapid eaters, reducing risks of bloating or obesity. Toys that mimic natural prey movements, such as laser pointers for cats or ball launchers for dogs, tap into instinctual behaviors and keep pets entertained. Rotating toys regularly keeps novelty high, maintaining your pet's interest and enhancing overall well-being."
