      "id": 7,
      "title": "How to Introduce a New Pet to Your Home",
      "type": "Behavior",
      "content": "Bringing a new pet into your home requires careful planning to reduce stress for both the newcomer and existing pets. Begin by isolating the new pet in a separate room with food, water, and litter box or bedding for a few days. Swap bedding or toys between pets to familiarize them with each other’s scent. Initial face-to-face introductions should be supervised and brief, gradually increasing interaction time if there are no signs of aggression. Providing positive reinforcement such as treats during meetings helps build positive associations. Patience is key, as some pets take weeks or months to fully accept each other."
