      "title": "Signs Your Pet Needs More Hydration",
      "type": "Health",
      "content": "Dehydration in pets can lead to serious health issues, including kidney failure. Common signs include dry or sticky gums, sunken eyes, lethargy, decreased skin elasticity, and reduced appetite. To encourage hydration, always provide fresh water in clean bowls, consider offering wet food, and use pet fountains which entice drinking through moving water. In hot climates or after exercise, increase water availability. If your pet shows severe dehydration symptoms, seek veterinary care immediately."
