      "type": "Safety",
      "content": "Many common houseplants are toxic to pets, causing symptoms from mild irritation to severe organ damage. Safe plants include spider plants, Boston ferns, bamboo palms, and African violets. Always research plants before bringing them home, and place plants out of reach to prevent chewing. If your pet ingests a toxic plant, contact a veterinarian immediately for advice and treatment."
