      "content": "Pets can exhibit stress through behavioral changes such as excessive licking, panting, hiding, pacing, or aggression. Stressors include loud noises, new environments, or changes in routine. Identifying and reducing these triggers helps maintain your pet’s mental health. Provide safe spaces, maintain consistent routines, and use calming aids like pheromone diffusers or anxiety wraps if necessary."
